# === ai-readiness-kg ===

# ── Secrets / environments ────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.venv
env/
venv/
ENV/

# ── Seldon / Claude Code working directories ──────────────────────────────
.claude/
.seldon/
handoffs/
.worktrees/
tmp/
# cc_tasks/ is intentionally TRACKED: task files are the work spec and travel
# with the repo (see icsp_notebook lineage).

# ── Corpus staging (harvester finds, pre-manifest; DD-003) ────────────────
# Documents are inert until an explicit manifest_add event. Staging never ships —
# except the committed run logs, which are provenance records, not staged content.
# (Ignore staging *contents*, not the dir node, so a specific file can be re-included.)
corpus/staging/*
!corpus/staging/pilot_adds_run_log.md

# ── Acquired corpus binaries (primary-source PDFs) ─────────────────────────
# Kept local, NOT committed to this public repo: some are third-party (arXiv author
# copyright). The provenance chain survives via each manifest entry's primary_url +
# content_hash + local_path (re-fetch + re-hash reproduces the file). Mirrors the
# icsp_notebook pattern for large/external source files.
corpus/pilot/
# Non-pilot acquired captures (Cisco methodology/instrument web printouts + merge
# components). Same rationale: third-party captures kept local; provenance in manifest.
corpus/cisco/

# ── Python ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
*.egg

# ── Test / coverage ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
coverage.xml
htmlcov/
.hypothesis/

# ── Linters / type checkers ───────────────────────────────────────────────
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pyre/
.pytype/

# ── Logs / backups ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
logs/
*.log
*.bak-*

# ── OS / IDE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
